    EC2

        - EC2  stands for elastic compute Cloud and is part of IAAS also known as infrastructure as a service, which essentially means the renting of an AWS machine or service.
        - EC2 is one of amazons highly popular services due to how flexible it is whether you are a start up or a large enterprise you can easlily scale up or own as needed and only pay for what you use.
        - EC2 allows for you to rent virtual machine, choose an operating system and configure them based on your needs. It also allows for you to store them on virtual drives (EBS) along side your VM ( virtual machnes) you need somewhere to store yor data thats where EBS (Elastic block store) comes in sort of like a hard drive for EC2 instances. 
        - When you've got multiple EC2 instances running at the same time you want to make sure that the traffic is shared evenly this is where Elastic load balances (ELB) comes in, it helps distribute the incoming requests to you instances so one machine isnt overloaded while others sit idle
        - EC2 also provides (ASG) also known as auto scaling group which ca scale your instances up or don depending on how much you need allowing you to uses only what you need, this can be very cost affective 


